name: mausoleum for a nameless courtesan
description: These burial chambers, nestled deep within the blockchain, could very well predate Elijah. A notebook entry from Sir Thomas Browne (1605-1682) suggests their occupants may have even been contemporaneous to Enoch's ascension into heaven. Even so, their names are lost to modernity, and what little we know of them, and of the civilisation to which they belonged, is gleaned entirely from arcane sources. We can only estimate how many more are out there.
